{
  "message": "fuzz: expand ioctl dispatch seed corpus for all command types\n\nThe fuzz_ioctl_dispatch target exercises the FUSE ioctl handler for\next4 and btrfs commands. Expand from 1 seed to 15 seeds covering:\n\n- FIEMAP, FIBMAP, FITRIM file operations\n- EXT4_IOC_GETFLAGS/GETVERSION for inode metadata\n- FS_IOC_GETFSUUID/GETFSXATTR/SETFSXATTR for filesystem metadata\n- FS_IOC_GET_ENCRYPTION_POLICY for fscrypt\n- EXT4_IOC_PRECACHE_EXTENTS for extent cache warmup\n- BTRFS_IOC_FS_INFO/DEV_INFO/INO_LOOKUP for btrfs-specific ioctls\n\nEach seed selects a different command path, ensuring the fuzzer\nexplores the full ioctl surface rather than focusing on one command.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
